step_data.thought: I successfully clicked on the 'SYSTEM' link in the navigation menu, and I can see that a dropdown menu has appeared with various system-related options. Based on the accessibility tree, the System menu is now expanded showing categories like 'Data Transfer', 'Extensions', 'Tools', 'Permissions', 'Action Logs', and 'Other Settings'. Each of these categories has sub-options. Since our goal is to navigate to the System section to manage configurations, tools, and technical settings, we're already in the right place. The menu is open and displaying all the System management options. I should inform the user that we've successfully navigated to the System section and highlight the available options.
step_data.action: stop('I have navigated to the System section. You now have access to manage various configurations, tools, and technical settings including: Data Transfer options (Import, Export), Extensions (Integrations), Tools (Cache Management, Index Management), Permissions (User management), Action Logs, and Other Settings (Notifications, Custom Variables, Encryption Key). You can click on any specific option to manage that particular aspect of the system.')
